description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen to join the Bowel Cancer Screening Team at SWBH. The successful applicants will join a long established, friendly team which provides a nurturing environment for applicants wishing to progress in their careers. We are looking for a friendly, hard-working, organised registered nurse, who has experience of working within gastroenterology. The successful applicant will be expected to work across 2 Trusts, encompassing 3 sites; City Hospital, Sandwell Hospital and Queen Elizabeth Hospital. Hours of work are covered over 4 days, but will include some evenings and occasional weekends. The successful candidates will also be given the opportunity to attend John Moores University, Liverpool, where they will be supported in gaining the mandatory Specialist Screening Practitioner qualification. This is an exciting time for Bowel Cancer Screening and a great opportunity for the right candidates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameClaire BeatsJob titleLead Specialist Screening PractitionerEmail addressclaire.beats@nhs.netTelephone number0121 507 3070Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note I only work Monday to Wednesday&lt;/p&gt;
